text:
20-24 West 71st Street, south side, west of Central Park West.
About 1911.
title: Manhattan: 71st Street (West) - Central Park West

text:
Central Park West, north from West 71st Street and showing apartment buildings facing Central Park. The Hotel Majestic is in the center, occupying the entire block front from 71st to 72nd Streets. On the left are the Lorington and the Barnard respectively.
September 1914.
George L. Balgue.
title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 71st Street (West)

text:
Central Park: Four mounted policemen on a bridle path in the southwestern part of the Park; the view is northwest towards Central Park West and 71st Street.

May 15, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: Central Park - Bridal path.

text:
Central Park West, west side, from 71st to 74th Streets. In the centre may be seen the erection of the Majestic Apartment House, rising on the site of the old Majestic Hotel. Immediately beyond it, from 72nd to 73rd Streets, is the Dakota, one of the oldest apartment houses in the city. The two apartment houses beyond the Dakota are the Langham and the San Remo.

January 8, 1931.

P. L. Sperr, Photographer.
title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 71st Street

text:
Erection of the Majestic Apartment House, on the site of the Majestic Hotel, Central Park West, west side, from 71st to 72nd Streets.
January 8, 1931.

P. L. Sperr, Photographer.
title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 71st Street

text:
The Majestic Apartment House, Central Park West, west side, from 71st to 72nd Streets, from Central Park. This building replaces the Majestic Hotel.

1932.
title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 71st Street

text:

Central Park: The Lake, a view southwest, showing Central Park West south from 71st Street.
May 17, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
Another view, from less of an elevation and at a narrower part of the lake. Notice the automobiles on the west or southbound driveway.
May 17, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.
